cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NE

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning algorithms and their resilience to Byzantine behavior. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple machines and network synchrony, which suggests that it may also belong to "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also introduces a novel filtering mechanism, which could fall under "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) or "cs.SY" (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses convergence and accuracy, which are key concerns in "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
